d 'WASSTEST': module to perform a two-sample Wasserstein Distance test for equality of distributions 
d
d  wasstest performs a two-sample Wasserstein distance permutation
d test to assess whether two samples come from the same
d distribution. The Wasserstein distance (also known as Earth
d Mover's Distance) measures the minimum "work" required to
d transform one distribution into another.  Unlike Cramer-von Mises
d and Anderson-Darling tests which focus on vertical differences
d between CDFs, the Wasserstein distance considers both vertical
d differences and the horizontal distances between points, making
d it sensitive to both location and spread differences. The
d permutation test provides an exact p-value by comparing the
d observed statistic to its distribution under random reassignment
d of group labels. 
d
d KW: equality of distributions
d KW: two-sample
d KW: comparisons
d
d Requires: Stata version 11
d
d Distribution-Date: 20251224
d
d Author: Ariel Linden, Linden Consulting Group, LLC
d Support: email alinden@@lindenconsulting.org
d
f wasstest.ado
